column1: Rule 1: Modifiers containing both carboxylic acid and amino groups, especially when they can form stable chelate complexes, tend to result in high yield.
column2: Rule 3: Modifiers containing aromatic heterocycles such as indole or benzofuran structures tend to result in high yield.
column3: Rule 6: Modifiers with formyl groups tend to result in low yield unless they are combined with adjacent electron-donating groups such as methoxy or amino groups, which can stabilize the catalyst interaction.
column4: Rule 7: Modifiers with trifluoromethyl groups tend to result in low yield.
